Product description

True Wireless Stereo Pairing

This handheld portable speaker is lightweight and colorful metal surface design. This X26M speaker is the mini size of the X26 speaker series . It delivers 5W output for each speaker. Sound is loud and clear for outdoor, camping, online meeting or showering. It’s IP65 waterproof and dustproof so you can keep listening rain or shine.

How to pair TWO small X26M speakers into stereo, delivers 10W output sound?

  1. Turn on both of your X26M speakers
  2. Long press about 2 second either speaker's triangle button "True Wireless Stereo button"
  3. You will hear prompt tone DI~DI, then light flash, speakers paired.
  4. Turn on your Bluetooth device to connect X26M.


Rechargeable Mini Speaker

X26m recharges with micro USB power sources. X26M gives you a 7 hours of playtime at 50% volume.

Charge time: 2h


Waterproof Portable Bluetooth Speaker

With IP65 certification the speaker can resist gentle water spray and splash but cannot be partially or fully submerged.


Wireless Bluethooth 5.3 & Support TF Card

Premium Bluetooth 5.3 technology effortlessly connects to all of your bluetooth-enabled devices up to 100ft range.

1. Support TF card play mode

2. Built in Microphone, answer phone calls with hands free function

Smaller Size, Bigger Sound

This mini wireless speaker is easy to use, sleek, ultra-compact design is perfect for on the go use - It’s light enough to carry in a backpack. Perfect for traveling, camping, boating, kayaking, outdoor adventure. Also, a good choice for kid's online class.

What's in the box?

1 x X26M speaker

1 x Charge cable

1 x Quick Start Guide

      Pleasant surprise. It worked with Windows 7
      Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2025
      Color: Pink
      I got this little speaker to use before falling asleep so I don't have to have the main computer speakers blaring. I am surprised it worked with Windows 7 on a 12-year old computer. The first time it came on the volume was LOUD. Whether it has long battery life and... See more
      I got this little speaker to use before falling asleep so I don't have to have the main computer speakers blaring. I am surprised it worked with Windows 7 on a 12-year old computer. The first time it came on the volume was LOUD. Whether it has long battery life and play time as advertised, I don't know yet. I am hopeful. I purchased the "pink" one so I could read the symbols on the bottom which are black. As it turns out though, once you press the middle button to turn it on, all the others light up, so it would not have been an issue after all. I have old Tracfone cell phones and have not yet tried it with those yet.

      Update: I tested it with the TracFone and that worked. I only got 6-8 hours of battery time while playing 3 podcasts.

      Update #2: I bought a 64GB TF card (SD card) and inserted it, then used my PC bluetooth program to load audios. It looked OK but then nothing would play. Then I realized one file was mp4 and THEN on my computer program I could not get the files to show up so I could delete them. The card did not show up in Windows Explorer either. Sigh
      Now it was time to use the adapter that came with the TF card. I did that and inserted it into my PC, was able to load files, and then voila they played on the speaker. However, any files I thought were already on there did not show up. I suppose I could verify one way or the other by checking how much space is taken up, but frankly at this point I don't care. LOL
      I'm new to bluetooth, obviously, so I again learned a lot.
      This is one powerful speaker. It's as if it has a motor inside and if I hold it I can feel serious vibrations.

      Update: the memory card works great. I suggest having tweezers handy to pull it out if you need to. I did discover that the speaker does not stop after the last audio; it replays in a loop.
      3 people found this helpful

      4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Affordable, good sound quality, USB-C charging, TF slot, TWS, and BT 5.3...
      Reviewed in the United States on March 3, 2025
      Color: Black
      I ordered two of these speakers not expecting much, as I just wanted to try out TWS on BT 5.3 without spending a lot of money. Amazingly, these are quite clear at maximum volume and they are loud for their size. I did not test the maximum distance apart nor their range as I... See more
      I ordered two of these speakers not expecting much, as I just wanted to try out TWS on BT 5.3 without spending a lot of money. Amazingly, these are quite clear at maximum volume and they are loud for their size. I did not test the maximum distance apart nor their range as I did not have these requirements... though there was no issue with the connection in a large room with a crowded 2.4Ghz WiFi spectrum from the neighbors. Songs played well with no lag between the speakers and button presses were very responsive and reacted quickly on the phone.

      Setup was relatively easy, but it could be made better by a second LED colour to let you know about pairing mode... and a different sound for TWS connections vs device connections. At least the pairing button is obvious and the power button will turn off both in a set of paired speakers. The USB-C charging ports and TF card slots are under a silicon cover near the base... so at least standards are supported and well-protected. The shape of the speaker would suit an auto cup holder even a smaller sized one... and they have a bit of heft for their size.

      I am rating these four stars, as they are a good value and they are much better than expected. As always, your mileage and preferences may vary...
